@gspencergoog if this is "as intended" then how does one effectively distinguish between a tap and a drag? 

BTW, "tap" historically refers to down followed by an up. If the framework means "tap down" then ideally that's what the API would say, e.g., `onTapDownOutside` (see `GestureDetector`).

But back to the issue at hand - I'm trying to use `onTapOutside` so that I can remove focus and close the IME when the user actually taps (down and up) outside. However, I don't want the keyboard to close when the user presses and drags to scroll the form. In that case, the user is just trying to scroll to another field, at which point the user will tap on that field. We don't want the keyboard closing during that scroll. Is there some other mechanism that's intended to be used for that purpose?

